column4: Musk says $35 000 Model 3 to reach volume production mid-year
column5: Tesla Inc Chief Executive Officer Elon Musk said on Monday production of the $35 000 version of the electric carmaker's Model 3 will start this month  but would not reach "volume production" until mid-year.

column4: RPT-UPDATE 1-Tesla's store-shuttering strategy may pull the rug out of solar
column5: SAN FRANCISCO  March 1 Tesla Inc's sudden decision to shutter the bulk of its stores around the world raises a red flag over the future of its solar branch  a declining business it paid $2.6 billion for in a controversial 2016 deal.

column4: Qualcomm launches patent challenge to Apple ahead of antitrust case
column5: Qualcomm Inc on Monday kicks off a patent challenge to Apple Inc  capping off a two-year legal strategy to put pressure on the iPhone maker before a major antitrust lawsuit between the two goes to trial in April.
